Made this for a dinner party and everyone raved about it. I took one reviewers suggestion to marinate in mustard, honey, dill, and I added Greek yogurt. I basted occasionally during grilling. It came out moist and tender.

Rating: 4
Way better than I thought it would be! Not something I would typically make, and the flavours were new to us as well. Took everyones advice and halved the water, The dijon had a great kick. The pickles were fun, my 3 year old giggled while eating them. The meat, pickles and sauce in one bite.... yum! My husband who is a health nut and can be picky - had seconds and then thirds! I roasted in the oven for 25 min at 350. Took out at 150 degrees and let rest for 10. It was perfect.

Rating: 3
I really wish I had followed the advice of many reviewers and eliminated or seriously cut back on the amount of water added to the sauce. It simply ran off the meat and into the grill. I threw it out and made a second batch of sauce with 1 T. water and served it with the cooked meat. The end product and the very good pickled zucchini made for a very tasty meal with plenty of leftovers for great sandwiches the next day.

