First review on this site....both the pork and the zucchini had a great flavor. Definitely not subtle. My wife doesn't eat pork, so I additionally grilled some chicken breasts for her with the sauce on it and she loved it. Next time I'll stick to 10 minutes marinating the zucchini. I went a while longer and the vinegar flavor was a little too strong. Also, I'll grill the pork over indirect heat, so the pork isn't as blackened.